Click on Launch Instance.
Choose an Amazon Machine Image (AMI): Select a Windows-based AMI (e.g., Windows Server 2022).
Choose an Instance Type: Choose an instance type suitable for Windows (e.g., t2.micro for free-tier).
Configure Key Pair:
Select an existing key pair or create a new one.
Configure Security Group:
Add an inbound rule to allow RDP (port 3389) for your IP or required range.
Launch the Instance.
Connect to the Instance via RDP:

After the instance is running, select it, and click on Connect.
Under RDP client, download the RDP file.
Retrieve the administrator password using your key pair.
Open the RDP file and log in using the administrator credentials.
2. Gather System Information
Once connected to the Windows instance:
Press Windows + R, type cmd, and press Enter to open the Command Prompt.
Type systeminfo and press Enter to display system details.                                                    
